WEBVTT

00:37.278 --> 00:40.109
Time-out! Time-out! Ref!
Ref! Time-out!

00:41.489 --> 00:45.010
Dean!

00:45.114 --> 00:46.667
All right, look alive.
Hustle up.

00:46.770 --> 00:50.050
All right, all right.
You have 44 seconds remaining.

00:50.153 --> 00:51.672
That's it. That's all you got.

00:51.775 --> 00:54.813
So forget the cheering,
the crowd, the recruiters.

00:54.916 --> 00:56.642
None of that exists.

00:56.746 --> 01:00.129
Dean, find the ball
and find Horse.

01:00.232 --> 01:01.613
- You got it, boss.
- Horse,

01:01.716 --> 01:03.063
find the basket.
- Mm-hmm.

01:03.166 --> 01:04.788
All right, let's go.
Steel Wolves, howl.

01:04.892 --> 01:06.066
Let's go, let's go, let's go!

01:06.169 --> 01:07.032
One. Two. Three!
- One. Two. Three!

01:08.413 --> 01:10.000
Move, move!

01:10.104 --> 01:11.347
- Yo, yo! Get it to Mason!
- Ball, ball, ball!

01:11.450 --> 01:12.865
- Horse is open!
- Yeah, yeah.

01:12.969 --> 01:14.004
Cut, cut, cut, cut, cut!

01:14.108 --> 01:16.593
Horse!

01:19.113 --> 01:20.287
- Yeah, let's go.
- Yeah!

01:20.390 --> 01:22.151
- Let's go, baby.
- Whoo-hoo!

01:22.254 --> 01:24.567
Yeah! You got this, Mason!

01:24.670 --> 01:25.878
- Whoo!
- Yeah!

01:25.982 --> 01:27.777
You got this, Mason!

01:30.987 --> 01:33.300
Mason...

01:33.403 --> 01:35.164
Horse!

01:37.925 --> 01:39.168
Go! Go! Go!

01:39.271 --> 01:41.204
I see him. Aah!

01:43.137 --> 01:44.863
Here, here! Horse!

01:48.177 --> 01:50.800
Shoot! Shoot!
Take your shot!

01:50.903 --> 01:53.320
Yes! Yes!

01:53.423 --> 01:54.804
Move it!

02:08.438 --> 02:10.544
Mason...

02:27.940 --> 02:30.150
- Yes!
- Yeah!

02:30.253 --> 02:32.462
Yes! Yeah!

02:38.986 --> 02:40.608
Hey, where the hell is Horse?

02:40.712 --> 02:41.954
- Steel Wolves!
- Steel Wolves!

03:00.387 --> 03:02.803
Mason...

03:10.293 --> 03:12.157
Mason...

03:21.580 --> 03:24.065
Please. Please, please!
Not yet!

03:24.169 --> 03:25.170
Okay?

03:29.070 --> 03:31.349
Look! Look!

03:34.317 --> 03:35.525
Look!

03:37.286 --> 03:39.805
See? See? It's gone!

03:39.909 --> 03:41.945
All right?

03:42.049 --> 03:43.775
Leave me alone!

04:06.453 --> 04:09.421
There he is!
The clutch king!

04:09.525 --> 04:11.147
Horse, you the man!
Yeah, yeah!

04:11.251 --> 04:12.459
Yeah!

04:12.562 --> 04:14.737
Let's go! Let's go!
Let's go, man!

04:14.840 --> 04:16.256
We thought we lost you
out there.

04:16.359 --> 04:18.085
That was a beautiful shot.

04:18.188 --> 04:19.500
You know that?
- Yeah.

04:29.130 --> 04:30.546
Horse!

04:30.649 --> 04:32.099
Come on, man!
You've been in there forever!

04:32.202 --> 04:33.825
You sure you're alone in there, pal?

04:33.928 --> 04:35.309
What's going on?
- Yeah.

04:35.413 --> 04:36.379
It's just me and your mo--

04:48.943 --> 04:51.014
Aaahhh!

04:58.159 --> 05:00.230
Horse! No!

05:00.334 --> 05:02.232
Quick, quick! Somebody help!

05:02.336 --> 05:04.200
Somebody help!

05:06.064 --> 05:08.031
Horse!

05:25.842 --> 05:29.708
♪ We're living
in desperate times ♪

05:29.812 --> 05:33.747
♪ These are desperate times,
my dear ♪

05:33.850 --> 05:37.716
♪ There's no way out of here

05:37.820 --> 05:41.617
♪ There's no way out, I fear

05:49.763 --> 05:53.491
♪ I've been holding back
all my tears ♪

05:53.594 --> 05:57.598
♪ Just so the pressure
don't show ♪

05:57.702 --> 06:01.706
♪ Like a time bomb
ticking away ♪

06:01.809 --> 06:05.710
♪ I might blow up someday

06:05.813 --> 06:09.438
♪ Don't push, don't shove

06:09.541 --> 06:12.924
♪ You better watch what you do

06:13.027 --> 06:15.098
♪ When my back's

06:15.202 --> 06:18.067
♪ To the wall

06:18.170 --> 06:20.863
♪ I might do anything at all

06:20.966 --> 06:23.141
♪ When my back's

06:23.244 --> 06:24.245
♪ To the wall

06:24.349 --> 06:25.833
♪ To the wall

06:25.937 --> 06:28.629
♪ I might take any chance
at all ♪

06:28.733 --> 06:31.080
♪ When my back's

06:31.183 --> 06:32.150
♪ To the wall

06:32.253 --> 06:34.083
♪ Back's to the wall

06:34.186 --> 06:37.258
♪ I might do anything

06:39.778 --> 06:43.403
♪ You've got the upper hand

06:43.506 --> 06:47.476
♪ Well, I've got nothing
to lose ♪

06:52.757 --> 06:53.896
Rise and shine!

06:53.999 --> 06:55.069
- Jesus, Rel!
- Whoa!

06:55.173 --> 06:56.346
What's the point of knocking

06:56.450 --> 06:57.865
if you're just gonna come in
anyways?

06:57.969 --> 06:59.591
Good to see you settled in, cuz.

06:59.695 --> 07:02.076
You know, like,
making the space your own.

07:02.180 --> 07:03.561
I mean, seriously, Chrys,

07:03.664 --> 07:05.045
if you need any help
unpacking the rest...

07:05.148 --> 07:06.909
I've been a lean,
mean drilling machine ever

07:07.012 --> 07:09.290
since I started working
weekends at the steel mill,

07:09.394 --> 07:12.293
so I'm always happy to help out.

07:12.397 --> 07:15.814
Oh, vinyls! Nice.

07:17.126 --> 07:19.577
Last time I saw you,
it was chart music.

07:19.680 --> 07:21.130
We were 11 years old, Rel.

07:21.233 --> 07:24.133
When did you get into
all this geriatric stuff?

07:24.236 --> 07:25.514
It doesn't get old...

07:25.617 --> 07:27.412
good music.
- Oh!

07:28.827 --> 07:30.415
It's only bad music
that ages.

07:30.519 --> 07:31.968
Well, let me know
when you want your pipe

07:32.072 --> 07:33.556
and slippers by the fire.

07:33.660 --> 07:35.385
You know,
your false teeth by the bedside.

07:35.489 --> 07:37.353
Oh! Oh.

07:37.457 --> 07:39.597
Smelly socks. Smelly socks.

07:39.700 --> 07:43.014
Anyway, we don't want to be late
on your first day.

07:43.117 --> 07:44.533
New school, new start.

07:44.636 --> 07:46.776
All that... good stuff.

07:48.398 --> 07:50.435
Okay, I'll go bring
the car around.

08:09.247 --> 08:11.525
♪ Cat got my tongue

08:11.629 --> 08:14.494
All right. Let's go.

08:14.597 --> 08:17.842
We've gotta hustle
if we don't want to be late.

08:17.945 --> 08:18.843
Oh, shit.

08:18.946 --> 08:20.741
I almost forgot "The Revenger."

08:20.845 --> 08:23.261
It might be a little different

08:23.364 --> 08:25.090
to your last school
back in Chicago,

08:25.194 --> 08:26.678
but, uh...

08:26.782 --> 08:29.025
welcome to Pellington High!

08:30.855 --> 08:33.340
Uh, look, Chrys, I know
you're my cousin and everything,

08:33.443 --> 08:35.756
but please don't feel like
you have to hang out with me

08:35.860 --> 08:37.758
or my fellow nerds.

08:37.862 --> 08:41.486
And... there's Grace.
She...

08:41.590 --> 08:43.177
She hangs out
with the populars now.

08:46.111 --> 08:49.080
♪ I broke a glass,
I tripped and fell ♪

08:49.183 --> 08:51.634
♪ I told secrets
I shouldn't tell ♪

08:51.738 --> 08:54.603
I'm not looking for a crowd,
Rel.

08:54.706 --> 08:56.881
- Okay.
- You're in my locker.

08:56.984 --> 09:00.091
Move.
- Hm! All right. Hm!

09:00.194 --> 09:03.370
♪ ...I'm alive

09:03.473 --> 09:10.377
♪ It's social suicide

09:10.480 --> 09:11.827
♪ Social suicide

09:11.930 --> 09:13.553
- Why does it say "Horse"?
- Huh?

09:13.656 --> 09:16.728
Oh, it's the nickname for,
uh, Mason Raymore.

09:16.832 --> 09:18.178
He's a kid who died--

09:18.281 --> 09:19.351
Ooh!

09:19.455 --> 09:21.215
You can't use this.

09:21.319 --> 09:22.838
They assigned me this locker.

09:22.941 --> 09:25.116
This school's got no respect
for the dead, bro.

09:25.219 --> 09:27.187
Pellington's been
around a long time, guys.

09:27.290 --> 09:28.913
All of these lockers
belong to dead people.

09:29.016 --> 09:31.778
Hey, Grace, your hair looks
really nice today.

09:33.262 --> 09:34.919
Thanks, Rel.

09:35.022 --> 09:37.887
Hey, who's your, uh... friend?

09:37.991 --> 09:39.302
Who? Oh.

09:39.406 --> 09:40.683
Oh, uh, no.

09:40.787 --> 09:42.478
Um, this is my cousin.

09:42.582 --> 09:44.791
Wait, wait, wait.

09:44.894 --> 09:46.309
You're the new girl?

09:48.001 --> 09:49.140
I heard...

09:49.243 --> 09:51.142
that she just got out
of junkie rehab

09:51.245 --> 09:54.663
after she killed her dad
or something like that.

09:54.766 --> 09:57.424
- Okay, cut it out, Dean.
- No, no, this is ridiculous.

09:57.527 --> 09:59.322
I mean,
the school has gone to hell.

09:59.426 --> 10:01.635
Maybe she was high
when she killed him, too.

10:01.739 --> 10:03.844
Shut up, Tanner.

10:03.948 --> 10:05.294
What?

10:05.397 --> 10:06.433
Well,
you should stop talking

10:06.536 --> 10:08.608
because
you don't know shit.

10:08.711 --> 10:09.954
Well, is it true?
Are you a junkie?

10:10.057 --> 10:11.887
I mean, you sure look like one

10:11.990 --> 10:14.510
with
the Goodwill jacket like this.

10:14.614 --> 10:15.925
- Oh!
- Yo!

10:16.029 --> 10:17.582
That's what's up!
That's my cousin, y'all!

10:17.686 --> 10:20.896
- Hey! Shut up, freak!
- Hey! That's enough!

10:20.999 --> 10:22.207
Enough!

10:23.726 --> 10:26.418
Ah. You four fighting
in the halls...

10:26.522 --> 10:28.558
detention, after school.

10:30.112 --> 10:32.735
This psychopath
just viciously attacked me,

10:32.839 --> 10:34.806
Mr. Craven.
- Let's start with detention.

10:34.910 --> 10:37.844
All right? And then we can
discuss suspension later.

10:37.947 --> 10:40.053
- Um, Mr. Craven?
- Yes?

10:40.156 --> 10:41.986
I saw what happened.
She didn't do anything.

10:42.089 --> 10:46.646
No, no, no. She kneed a boy
in his genital bag, Miss Gains.

10:46.749 --> 10:48.371
This is indeed something.
- No. I--

10:48.475 --> 10:53.031
Shh, shh. And for forcing
your unsought opinion upon me,

10:53.135 --> 10:55.516
you can join us in detention,
as well.

10:55.620 --> 10:58.381
Okay? Good. See you all later.

10:58.485 --> 11:00.660
See you there.

11:00.763 --> 11:02.247
Well,
there goes our pool date, babe.

11:02.351 --> 11:03.835
Nice work.
- You think they're still good

11:03.939 --> 11:05.734
for making babies?
- Gross.

11:05.837 --> 11:07.114
Hey. I'm serious.

11:07.218 --> 11:08.737
That was awesome.

11:10.600 --> 11:12.395
Uh, look,
you're gonna be okay, right?

11:12.499 --> 11:14.915
Yeah? Yeah? Okay.
Have a good day!

11:16.192 --> 11:18.608
Hey.
I'm sorry about what they said.

11:18.712 --> 11:19.886
Oh, don't be. I mean...

11:19.989 --> 11:21.888
they're not wrong
about any of it.

11:22.992 --> 11:25.132
Um... oh.
Hang on. I'll help you.

11:25.236 --> 11:26.789
I don't-- I don't need
your help.

11:30.310 --> 11:31.414
Okay.

11:51.503 --> 11:54.506
Chrysanthemum...

12:40.621 --> 12:43.728
Chrysanthemum...

12:53.117 --> 12:54.635
Come on,
we've only got an hour.

12:54.739 --> 12:56.361
Let's not waste it.

12:56.465 --> 13:00.365
Ah. Nice of you to join us.

13:00.469 --> 13:01.711
Chrysanthemum.

13:01.815 --> 13:05.543
Chrysanthemum? Fuck.

13:05.646 --> 13:07.441
It's Chrys, actually.

13:07.545 --> 13:08.926
Ooh!

13:11.687 --> 13:13.344
Whoa! What is that?

13:13.447 --> 13:15.346
Is that a pipe?

13:15.449 --> 13:17.072
- No.
- Uh, Mr. Craven?

13:17.175 --> 13:18.901
- Yes, Dean?
- Question--

13:19.005 --> 13:21.904
Are we allowed, like,
drug paraphernalia in school?

13:22.008 --> 13:24.010
You know, especially
when someone identifies

13:24.113 --> 13:25.666
as, like, a junkie.

13:25.770 --> 13:28.324
- It's not a pipe.
- Hey, bring it to me.

13:29.878 --> 13:31.569
I found it in my locker.

13:33.778 --> 13:35.711
Oh. Wow.

13:37.851 --> 13:38.887
Do you think
it's worth anything?

13:38.990 --> 13:40.371
I don't know.

13:40.474 --> 13:43.339
It's like a musical instrument,
doesn't it?

13:43.443 --> 13:46.101
Some kind of whistle
or a kazoo.

13:46.204 --> 13:48.931
I mean,
this is certainly early Mayan,

13:49.035 --> 13:51.796
but the rest,
I mean... I don't know.

13:51.900 --> 13:53.522
Could be Olmec.

13:53.625 --> 13:55.075
Can you translate any of it?

13:55.179 --> 13:58.768
I don't know. Let's--
Let's have a look.

13:58.872 --> 14:00.218
All right.

14:00.322 --> 14:02.220
It's been a long time
since grad school.

14:02.324 --> 14:03.877
Oh, look. There's a word here.

14:03.981 --> 14:06.397
That would be pronounced
"K'aaba"...

14:06.500 --> 14:09.020
uh, which means "to talk"

14:09.124 --> 14:13.680
or it can also mean
"to call out to."

14:13.783 --> 14:15.233
There's another word
on this side.

14:15.337 --> 14:17.408
That might be "Pixan."

14:17.511 --> 14:18.927
Do you spell that P-I-C?

14:19.030 --> 14:20.998
Uh, no. "P"...
It looks like...

14:21.101 --> 14:24.725
to be P-I-X-A-N.

14:24.829 --> 14:25.795
Why?
What are you doing?

14:27.728 --> 14:29.489
"Summon the dead."

14:29.592 --> 14:31.387
Wow. Hmm.

14:31.491 --> 14:33.148
You don't even need
a degree anymore.

14:33.251 --> 14:35.805
You just
And that's it.

14:35.909 --> 14:37.359
Look,
I shouldn't have even--

14:37.462 --> 14:40.465
Ah, I think I should
probably look after this.

14:40.569 --> 14:45.091
It could actually,
uh, have huge historical value.

14:45.194 --> 14:46.575
And-- And you did say

14:46.678 --> 14:48.301
you took it
out of a school-property locker.

14:48.404 --> 14:51.131
It doesn't belong to you.
Good. All right.

14:51.235 --> 14:52.546
Look, I think that's
probably a good place

14:52.650 --> 14:53.927
to end detention for the day.

14:54.031 --> 14:55.273
- Ah!
- Yep. Yep.

14:55.377 --> 14:57.103
- Thank you, Mr. Craven.
- Great idea.

14:57.206 --> 15:01.417
Instead, I would like you
to write a five-page essay

15:01.521 --> 15:04.213
on the role
of pre-prepared sacrifice

15:04.317 --> 15:05.974
in ancient Mesoamerica.

15:06.077 --> 15:08.045
- Seriously?
- Do six. Six pages.

15:08.148 --> 15:09.736
No, no. It's fine, it's fine.
We're going.

15:09.839 --> 15:11.358
- Yeah.
- We're out.

15:13.602 --> 15:15.673
Hey. Um,
we're all meeting at Grace's

15:15.776 --> 15:18.918
to watch her compose a six-page
haiku on blood sacrifices.

15:19.021 --> 15:20.643
So I'll see you guys at 7:00?

15:20.747 --> 15:22.266
You mean
we're all invited now?

15:22.369 --> 15:25.786
Yeah, Baby Dean,
we're all invited.

15:25.890 --> 15:27.409
Even you.

15:27.512 --> 15:29.100
It's called being welcoming
and not an asshole.

15:30.584 --> 15:31.896
All right, I'll drive.

15:32.000 --> 15:33.484
I want to make it home
in one piece.

15:34.864 --> 15:36.280
I'll see you guys there.

15:37.626 --> 15:39.697
Got a crush on Grace, huh?

15:39.800 --> 15:41.423
Yeah.

15:43.321 --> 15:46.462
One day, I'll take my shot.

16:03.963 --> 16:05.792
Whoa.

16:25.191 --> 16:29.091
Craven.
Craven...

16:31.024 --> 16:33.889
Hey, um, listen...

16:33.993 --> 16:35.718
about this morning...

16:35.822 --> 16:38.100
They had no right
to talk about what happened

16:38.204 --> 16:39.895
to your dad like that.

16:39.999 --> 16:42.415
I mean, it's fine.

16:42.518 --> 16:44.382
It wasn't your fault.
You know?

16:44.486 --> 16:47.006
I really don't
want to talk about it.

16:49.284 --> 16:51.769
Yeah. Yeah. Yeah, okay.

16:51.872 --> 16:57.119
So... how was your first day
at Pellington High?

16:57.223 --> 17:00.778
Um, Ellie seems nice.

17:00.881 --> 17:02.262
Oh, my God.

17:02.366 --> 17:05.024
I mean, she's nothing special,
but, like...

17:06.887 --> 17:08.268
"Revenger."

17:09.476 --> 17:11.133
Oh! Okay.

17:20.349 --> 17:22.489
Ah. Good.

17:35.744 --> 17:36.779
Hm.

17:36.883 --> 17:38.954
Ah.

17:41.715 --> 17:43.027
Ah.

17:44.891 --> 17:46.168
Hm.

17:49.378 --> 17:50.621
Hm.

17:52.726 --> 17:55.867
That's...

17:55.971 --> 17:58.077
more than a kazoo.

17:59.768 --> 18:01.666
Huh.

18:10.089 --> 18:13.609
We've got a major traffic
collision. There's two bodies.

18:13.713 --> 18:15.404
One male fatality.

18:15.508 --> 18:18.166
Are you okay?

18:18.269 --> 18:20.996
I didn't mean to surprise you.

18:21.100 --> 18:22.722
You just started here?

18:22.825 --> 18:24.862
That obvious, huh?

18:24.965 --> 18:26.450
A little bit.

18:26.553 --> 18:29.211
Noah... Haggerty.

18:29.315 --> 18:32.628
I'm the youth pastor
down at St. Marks.

18:32.732 --> 18:34.320
You worship?

18:34.423 --> 18:36.977
I'm not really into religion.

18:37.081 --> 18:39.014
Ah. Me neither.

18:39.118 --> 18:40.740
I am into God, though.

18:43.639 --> 18:45.848
You should come by my church
sometime.

18:45.952 --> 18:48.610
Get to know a few people.
They're good people.

18:48.713 --> 18:51.026
Real people loving Jesus.
Right?

18:54.754 --> 18:56.204
But, also, you know...

18:58.275 --> 19:00.000
...down for a good time.

19:00.104 --> 19:01.657
Being new in town,

19:01.761 --> 19:03.935
you might not know where to go
if you need something.

19:04.039 --> 19:06.041
I don't.

19:06.145 --> 19:08.871
Well, sure, sure. I get it.

19:08.975 --> 19:10.459
You're clean.

19:10.563 --> 19:13.462
But if you ever want to get
a little dirty...

19:13.566 --> 19:17.846
Look, how about
a welcome-to-town gift?

19:20.780 --> 19:23.541
Hey,
get the fuck away from her!

19:23.645 --> 19:24.749
- Hey!
- Oh!

19:24.853 --> 19:26.337
Stop!

19:29.064 --> 19:31.618
God has a job for everyone.

19:31.722 --> 19:33.551
I'm just trying
to help those in need.

19:35.898 --> 19:38.038
Okay?

19:38.142 --> 19:40.662
Okay.

19:40.765 --> 19:43.458
So no harm, no foul.

19:43.561 --> 19:44.976
I'm always here if you need me.

19:46.081 --> 19:49.705
- Ah!
- Are you okay?

19:49.809 --> 19:51.086
I'm fine.

19:57.955 --> 19:59.819
Hey, so that preacher...

19:59.922 --> 20:01.993
he's a sound character, huh?

20:04.858 --> 20:09.725
Funny thing is, parents
send their kids to his church...

20:09.829 --> 20:11.555
think he's a role model.

20:11.658 --> 20:14.040
He's not just a creep, though.

20:14.143 --> 20:16.180
He sells drugs to the kids.

20:16.284 --> 20:18.527
And a year ago,
one of them OD'd.

20:19.701 --> 20:22.738
One day, he's gonna get
what's his.

20:22.842 --> 20:24.292
Let's get out of here.

20:36.614 --> 20:38.961
Ah.

20:39.065 --> 20:40.515
Hm.

20:48.695 --> 20:50.007
Hm.

20:58.740 --> 21:00.880
Aah!

21:03.262 --> 21:04.539
Fuck...

21:04.642 --> 21:05.919
Whoo!

21:06.023 --> 21:07.783
- What's up?
- Hey.

21:07.887 --> 21:09.751
Have you guys got
our essay finished yet?

21:09.854 --> 21:12.409
- What happened to your face?
- What?

21:12.512 --> 21:14.238
Oh, it was run-in
with Noah Haggerty.

21:14.342 --> 21:16.620
It was nothing. Anyway...

21:16.723 --> 21:18.553
look what I got.

21:21.245 --> 21:23.799
Ta-da!

21:30.737 --> 21:31.945
Fuck!

21:41.300 --> 21:42.611
Charlie?

21:51.171 --> 21:52.621
Charlie.

22:10.087 --> 22:12.020
Charlie?

22:19.199 --> 22:20.891
Charlie.

22:45.053 --> 22:47.296
I'm afraid the school
is closed, sir.

22:47.400 --> 22:49.160
You're-- You're trespassing.

22:51.749 --> 22:55.650
I've called security already,
so...

22:55.753 --> 22:57.859
you'd better be on your way.

23:04.141 --> 23:05.453
- Mr. Craven?
- Fucking hell!

23:05.556 --> 23:07.627
- Are you okay?
- Oh, my God!

23:07.731 --> 23:09.629
I called your name, but...

23:09.733 --> 23:11.907
You need to sit down
for a minute?

23:12.011 --> 23:13.461
Catch your breath?

23:13.564 --> 23:16.843
No, no, no. I'm fine.
I just think I've been...

23:16.947 --> 23:19.467
just working a bit too much
recently.

23:20.951 --> 23:21.986
Good.

23:27.233 --> 23:29.304
Oh, Mr. Craven?

23:29.408 --> 23:30.926
Your secret's safe with me.

23:31.030 --> 23:32.065
What's that?

23:38.658 --> 23:41.868
♪ It's an omen

23:42.662 --> 23:45.562
I want to summon my grandpa.

23:45.665 --> 23:47.564
But your grandpa's not dead.

23:47.667 --> 23:50.394
But he's, like, really old.
And he makes this,

23:50.498 --> 23:52.603
like, amazing hooch.
- Timmy, go to your room!

23:52.707 --> 23:54.950
He's such a little freak.

23:55.054 --> 23:58.920
♪ Now the writing's
on the wall ♪

23:59.023 --> 24:00.991
Oh, Chrys.

24:01.094 --> 24:02.682
♪ It's an omen

24:02.786 --> 24:06.168
You know,
it's really kind of beautiful.

24:06.272 --> 24:08.377
If working in the E.R.
has taught me anything,

24:08.481 --> 24:10.207
it's that death is
never beautiful.

24:10.310 --> 24:12.451
I am not going to die.

24:12.554 --> 24:15.039
Oh!
Why didn't I think of that?

24:34.783 --> 24:35.543
Oh!

24:57.392 --> 24:59.498
Craven...

25:17.274 --> 25:19.518
Okay, boys and girls.

25:20.657 --> 25:23.522
Let's think about
the dearly departed.

25:23.625 --> 25:25.558
Go for it, babe. I dare you.

25:25.662 --> 25:27.318
I think I'm gonna pass
on the whole

25:27.422 --> 25:29.458
ghost-summoning death whistle.

25:29.562 --> 25:31.357
- Bye, Chrysanthemum.
- Bye.

25:31.460 --> 25:33.186
- Bye!
- Hey.

25:33.290 --> 25:34.429
You don't have to leave.

25:34.533 --> 25:36.776
Oh, I...I have to unpack.

25:36.880 --> 25:40.055
Come on, babe. I mean, what's
the worst that can happen?

25:50.928 --> 25:52.965
It's okay.
I should just go.

26:20.026 --> 26:21.372
That was, uh...

26:23.547 --> 26:24.928
...intense.

26:30.002 --> 26:31.072
Now what?

26:32.245 --> 26:33.626
Wait. Wait, wait.

26:36.353 --> 26:37.803
Listen. You guys hear that?

26:42.428 --> 26:44.085
I think I heard
something coming.

26:58.789 --> 27:00.239
- Oh! What?! Oh!
- Dean!

27:00.342 --> 27:01.861
Ugh! Asshole!

27:01.965 --> 27:03.794
Oh, my God.
- You're so gross!

27:03.898 --> 27:06.176
- Ugh!
- Okay, on that note, I'm out.

27:06.279 --> 27:07.522
It's not funny.

27:07.626 --> 27:10.490
Look, I told you
it was all bullshit.

27:10.594 --> 27:11.802
All right?

27:15.564 --> 27:16.876
Hey!

27:20.569 --> 27:22.641
Sorry if it was weird tonight.

27:23.400 --> 27:25.574
Uh, you should come tomorrow.

27:26.265 --> 27:29.302
It's the annual
Pellington Harvest Festival.

27:29.406 --> 27:31.891
Caramel apples, pumpkin carving,

27:31.995 --> 27:33.652
spooky hay bale maze.

27:33.755 --> 27:35.308
It's fun.

27:35.412 --> 27:36.896
And we always go.

27:37.000 --> 27:39.381
And it's probably the last year
we'll all be together

27:39.485 --> 27:43.454
before we go off to lead our
incredibly serious adult lives.

27:44.697 --> 27:46.492
Sounds cute.

27:46.595 --> 27:50.358
Yeah, I'd just... like it if
you came.

27:54.258 --> 27:55.190
Yo, Ellie!

27:55.294 --> 27:57.123
You left your, uh...

27:57.227 --> 27:58.262
Thanks.

27:59.401 --> 28:00.679
Diabetic.

28:01.507 --> 28:03.440
My medicines.

28:03.543 --> 28:05.131
I'm late for my shift,
but, um...

28:05.235 --> 28:07.202
Uh, text me
about the Harvest Fest.

28:07.306 --> 28:08.376
Rel has my number.

28:08.479 --> 28:09.688
Okay.

28:18.041 --> 28:20.388
Rel, is she straight?

28:23.253 --> 28:24.461
I don't know.

28:25.634 --> 28:27.429
Never been super apparent.

28:29.673 --> 28:31.606
But, uh...

28:31.710 --> 28:34.264
something tells me
we're gonna find out.

28:36.335 --> 28:39.510
♪ In the dark
and lonely night ♪

28:39.614 --> 28:42.617
♪ I gave my heart to you

28:48.416 --> 28:54.698
♪ Now I'm dreaming of a love
known only by we two ♪

29:00.669 --> 29:03.569
♪ You didn't want my heart
to keep ♪

29:03.672 --> 29:06.710
♪ Now our love's drifted away

29:12.820 --> 29:15.823
♪ And in shadows of the night

29:15.926 --> 29:19.136
♪ My heart it will remain

29:23.692 --> 29:25.073
Nope.

29:25.177 --> 29:30.769
♪ In the night
is where we met, and ♪

29:30.872 --> 29:36.809
♪ In the night is
where we parted ♪

29:36.913 --> 29:43.402
♪ In the night is
where we'll meet again ♪

29:43.505 --> 29:46.785
♪ If only in my dreams

29:49.028 --> 29:52.204
♪ But the night is on my side

29:52.307 --> 29:54.827
♪ Your thoughts
will turn to me ♪

30:01.247 --> 30:04.181
♪ In the moments you're alone

30:04.285 --> 30:06.908
♪ Before you fall asleep...

30:14.019 --> 30:15.434
I got us hot chocolate!

30:15.537 --> 30:17.125
Knock, please!

30:17.229 --> 30:20.059
- Whoa! Sorry.
- There's someone watching.

30:20.163 --> 30:23.062
Here. It's hot. Careful.

30:23.166 --> 30:25.306
I thought I saw someone
in the tree.

30:26.997 --> 30:29.724
I don't see anyone.

30:29.828 --> 30:32.347
Probably your eyes
playing tricks on you.

30:34.418 --> 30:35.730
Oh, God.

30:35.834 --> 30:37.697
Oh, God. Oh, no.

30:37.801 --> 30:40.493
- What?
- I accidentally texted Ellie.

30:41.425 --> 30:43.082
- Oh, shit.
- I gotta leave town, I gotta go.

30:43.186 --> 30:45.015
Yeah, that... that is...

30:45.119 --> 30:46.396
Yeah. That's bad.

30:46.499 --> 30:47.915
Yeah, you think?

30:48.018 --> 30:49.192
What do I say?

30:49.295 --> 30:50.952
- Uh... uh...
- What do I say?

30:51.056 --> 30:53.092
Um, pretend
someone stole your phone.

30:53.196 --> 30:54.818
Yeah, and emotionally sexted

30:54.922 --> 30:56.751
a girl that I met
less than 24 hours ago?

30:56.855 --> 30:58.028
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

30:58.132 --> 31:00.686
- Yeah, that works.
- Mm, yeah, sure.

31:01.549 --> 31:03.827
Typing... Oh, yeah.
She's-- she's texting back.

31:03.931 --> 31:05.173
Um...

31:07.969 --> 31:09.350
Question mark?

31:10.799 --> 31:12.491
Why question mark?
What do I say?

31:12.594 --> 31:13.802
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

31:13.906 --> 31:17.496
Be casual, okay? Just chill.

31:17.599 --> 31:18.669
Okay?

31:18.773 --> 31:20.568
Whatever you do...

31:20.671 --> 31:23.226
don't act desperate.

31:23.329 --> 31:24.503
Okay.

31:25.538 --> 31:26.781
Mm.

31:26.885 --> 31:28.956
"If you're lucky."

31:29.059 --> 31:31.682
What? What?! No!

31:31.786 --> 31:34.996
Casual, not Kardashian.

31:36.032 --> 31:36.998
Let's see...

31:37.102 --> 31:39.794
"See you then."

31:39.898 --> 31:42.348
- "See you then"?
- Boom.

31:42.452 --> 31:45.662
Looks like someone's going
to the Harvest Festival.

31:45.765 --> 31:47.181
Mm?

31:47.284 --> 31:53.014
♪ In the night is when
we'll meet again ♪

31:53.118 --> 31:55.016
♪ If only in my dreams

31:55.120 --> 31:56.673
What am I doing?

31:59.227 --> 32:04.060
♪ If only in my dreams

32:05.268 --> 32:08.650
♪ If only in my dreams

32:11.205 --> 32:18.591
♪ If only in my dreams

32:19.558 --> 32:22.112
You, my friend,
should not be driving.

32:22.216 --> 32:25.322
Me, my friend,
I'm focused, motherfucker.

32:26.496 --> 32:28.877
I mean, we made it home,
didn't we?

32:28.981 --> 32:30.431
Watch this, watch this.

32:30.534 --> 32:31.604
He shoots...

32:33.848 --> 32:35.194
He does not score!

32:35.298 --> 32:38.266
Story of your life, LeBron.

32:39.233 --> 32:40.475
Fuck you, bro.

32:40.579 --> 32:42.339
I'll, uh...
I'll see you at school?

32:42.443 --> 32:43.444
- Yeah.
- LeBron.

32:43.547 --> 32:44.824
Kiss my ass, bitch.

32:44.928 --> 32:46.343
- Kiss your mom's.
- Steel Wolves howl!

32:46.447 --> 32:47.413
- What?
- Huh?

33:15.959 --> 33:18.099
Gracey...

33:19.031 --> 33:20.999
Timmy, I hear you!

33:28.730 --> 33:30.422
Timmy! Knock it off!

33:51.132 --> 33:52.409
Hello?

34:19.022 --> 34:20.265
Timmy?

34:28.859 --> 34:31.655
Gracey...

34:34.002 --> 34:35.211
Dean?

34:36.695 --> 34:38.110
Is that you?

34:41.009 --> 34:42.459
This isn't funny.

35:04.895 --> 35:05.793
Timmy!

35:07.933 --> 35:09.417
Mom says you should
come in now

35:09.521 --> 35:11.557
or you'll turn into a prune.

35:32.923 --> 35:34.442
Where is everybody?

35:37.445 --> 35:39.654
Come on. Let's go.

35:48.767 --> 35:51.183
We will have
grief counselors available

35:51.287 --> 35:54.255
if any student needs someone
to talk to.

35:54.359 --> 35:56.706
This is hard on all of us.

35:56.809 --> 35:59.536
Mr. Craven was a dedicated
member of the Pellington...

35:59.640 --> 36:01.020
What's going on?

36:01.124 --> 36:02.608
Mr. Craven died last night.

36:02.712 --> 36:04.679
What? How?

36:04.783 --> 36:07.717
Turns out he had
stage four lung cancer.

36:07.820 --> 36:11.410
Dr. Wells said it's amazing he
was even on his feet yesterday.

36:11.514 --> 36:14.689
I guess we won't have to write
that paper anymore.

36:14.793 --> 36:16.726
But he will be missed.

36:16.829 --> 36:18.969
I'm sure Mr. Craven
would want you to know

36:19.073 --> 36:20.868
how much he loved teaching here,

36:20.971 --> 36:23.802
and how grateful he was
to give so many years

36:23.905 --> 36:26.218
of his life to this school.

36:26.322 --> 36:28.531
Both Mr. Craven
and Mason Raymore

36:28.634 --> 36:29.980
were proud members of the...

36:48.516 --> 36:50.000
Ellie...

36:50.104 --> 36:51.070
Chrys...

36:51.174 --> 36:52.382
You forgot this last night.

36:52.486 --> 36:54.039
- It's not mine.
- I don't want it.

36:54.142 --> 36:56.317
Gives me the creeps.

36:56.421 --> 36:59.044
I say you throw
that voodoo shit out.

36:59.147 --> 37:00.528
It's bad news.
- I know this pawn shop

37:00.632 --> 37:02.289
on the East Side, actually.
We could...

37:02.392 --> 37:04.152
Or we could just return it
to Mason's family.

37:04.256 --> 37:05.706
Yeah.

37:05.809 --> 37:08.536
Yeah, I agree. Um...

37:08.640 --> 37:10.745
Yeah, no, that-- that was
my next suggestion, too.

37:10.849 --> 37:12.920
I can-- I can drive
if you want.

37:21.653 --> 37:24.000
Do you design them yourself?

37:26.658 --> 37:28.936
Why do you hide them?
They're beautiful.

37:29.039 --> 37:31.835
Um, I don't know.
I guess they're personal.

37:32.733 --> 37:34.942
I always wanted to get
a tattoo.

37:35.045 --> 37:37.289
My mom would never let me.

37:37.393 --> 37:39.602
How do you know
what you want to design?

37:41.397 --> 37:43.640
I guess you just find
something you love

37:43.744 --> 37:46.505
and you let it scar you
for life.

37:48.127 --> 37:50.578
- That easy, huh?
- Mm. Easy.

37:53.995 --> 37:55.273
Look at this place.

38:34.760 --> 38:35.968
Hello?

38:37.591 --> 38:39.109
The door was open.

38:54.608 --> 38:59.129
♪ Folks, I'm going down
to St. James Infirmary ♪

39:01.373 --> 39:06.551
♪ See my baby there

39:06.654 --> 39:09.554
♪ She's stretched out
on a long white table ♪

39:09.657 --> 39:12.142
We have something
that belonged to Mason.

39:12.246 --> 39:16.940
♪ So sweet, so cold, so fair

39:18.459 --> 39:20.219
I was born in this house.

39:24.120 --> 39:27.157
I hoped to die here, too.

39:29.401 --> 39:32.508
But the bank says
it's not even mine anymore.

39:32.611 --> 39:33.854
I'm sorry, we were just...

39:33.957 --> 39:35.338
Maybe I'll get lucky

39:35.442 --> 39:37.513
and drop dead today.

39:39.342 --> 39:41.448
Memento mori.

39:41.551 --> 39:44.865
Reminders of mortality.

39:44.968 --> 39:46.867
It's all got to go.

39:48.593 --> 39:51.112
I traveled the world
collecting them.

39:51.216 --> 39:56.497
Every culture, every faith
and philosophy have their own.

39:56.601 --> 39:58.948
Some wrestling with death,

39:59.051 --> 40:01.088
others dancing with it.

40:03.021 --> 40:04.919
Is this a part
of your collection?

40:05.023 --> 40:07.543
I found it
in Mason Raymore's locker.

40:08.578 --> 40:11.201
You didn't find it.

40:11.305 --> 40:13.549
It found you.

40:13.652 --> 40:16.241
Like it found my grandson.

40:16.344 --> 40:18.105
Like it found me.

40:21.177 --> 40:22.903
Half a lifetime ago.

40:23.006 --> 40:25.768
A back-alley market
in Guatemala.

40:25.871 --> 40:29.081
It took my grandson,
my daughter.

40:29.185 --> 40:30.876
And it will take more.

40:30.980 --> 40:32.878
What is it?

40:32.982 --> 40:34.466
In Choka.

40:36.261 --> 40:37.642
The cry.

40:39.091 --> 40:42.888
A stolen treasure
from a plundered people.

40:43.751 --> 40:47.445
We were told the markings said
"summon the dead"?

40:49.412 --> 40:50.724
No...

40:52.484 --> 40:54.244
Not quite.

40:54.348 --> 40:55.970
The markings read...

40:56.074 --> 40:58.594
"summon yourdeath."

41:00.388 --> 41:02.874
The day you are born...

41:02.977 --> 41:04.634
so is your death.

41:04.738 --> 41:08.189
From that day on,
she is searching for you.

41:08.293 --> 41:10.571
If you're fated to die at 90,

41:10.675 --> 41:13.229
it will take her 90 years
to find you.

41:13.332 --> 41:16.335
Fated to die at 30, only 30.

41:16.439 --> 41:18.959
But if you hear the whistle
scream,

41:19.062 --> 41:21.582
it changes all that.

41:21.686 --> 41:24.965
A call from In Choka
guides your death.

41:26.553 --> 41:29.072
So she finds you earlier.

41:30.557 --> 41:32.179
What does it look like?

41:33.145 --> 41:34.284
Death.

41:34.388 --> 41:36.597
Like you, of course.

41:36.701 --> 41:38.599
You will become
what you would have been

41:38.703 --> 41:40.256
in your last breath.

41:47.332 --> 41:48.747
Keep this.

41:49.886 --> 41:52.130
It was never mine to take.

41:55.409 --> 41:57.066
What if I don't want to die?

41:59.206 --> 42:01.519
Then you shouldn't
have been born.

42:03.417 --> 42:04.694
I mean, you saw her.

42:04.798 --> 42:06.213
She's on a lot of meds.

42:06.316 --> 42:07.455
And she just lost her family.

42:07.559 --> 42:09.147
That'll rattle anyone.

42:11.459 --> 42:13.461
And speaking
as future Dr. Gains,

42:13.565 --> 42:15.084
I mean, there's
no medical science

42:15.187 --> 42:16.154
behind what she's saying.

42:16.257 --> 42:18.156
Oh, yeah, no.

42:18.259 --> 42:19.882
I know.

42:19.985 --> 42:22.194
It was bullshit.

42:22.298 --> 42:23.679
Mostly.

42:25.439 --> 42:30.548
But do you think that
Mr. Craven used it like Mason?

42:33.585 --> 42:35.035
Maybe.

42:35.138 --> 42:37.244
Their files will be
at the hospital I work at.

42:37.347 --> 42:38.901
We'll find something there.

43:02.925 --> 43:05.652
When you mentioned Mason,
it gave me an idea.

43:06.584 --> 43:07.792
Whoa.

43:07.895 --> 43:09.276
There's something
about his death

43:09.379 --> 43:10.967
that just never added up.

43:11.071 --> 43:12.831
He caught on fire
in a shower cubicle,

43:12.935 --> 43:15.351
and they blamed it
on a gas leak.

43:18.630 --> 43:20.011
There. Raymore.

43:27.570 --> 43:30.953
They had to use his dental
records to confirm his identity.

43:32.402 --> 43:34.439
Oh, God.

43:34.542 --> 43:36.752
He was so badly burned.

43:37.925 --> 43:39.478
I just need to check
a patient's records...

43:39.582 --> 43:41.342
Shit!

43:43.137 --> 43:44.691
Shh!

43:44.794 --> 43:46.382
Shit!

44:10.578 --> 44:13.271
"Bone structure suggests
late 40s."

44:14.341 --> 44:17.793
Ellie, how old was Mason
when he died?

44:27.457 --> 44:29.356
Ellie. What's his age?

44:30.391 --> 44:33.291
Uh, 17. Why?

44:34.050 --> 44:36.674
Because the coroner's report
says late 40s.

44:43.301 --> 44:46.373
"You will become what you would
have been in your last breath."

44:47.823 --> 44:51.930
So Mason would have died when
he was older from the gas leak?

44:52.034 --> 44:55.693
Yeah. Mr. Craven, that cancer
would've killed him eventually.

44:55.796 --> 44:58.454
I'd give him
another 10 to 15 years.

44:58.557 --> 45:00.870
Yeah, but not last night.

45:02.354 --> 45:04.184
This is Dr. Andrews...

45:04.287 --> 45:07.463
Someone's been in the records
room messing with the files.

45:07.566 --> 45:09.845
- Ellie...
- Check the system to see
who was in here...

45:09.948 --> 45:11.398
We all heard that whistle.

45:11.501 --> 45:13.434
Thanks.

45:16.058 --> 45:17.611
We need to warn the others.

45:17.715 --> 45:19.371
They'll be at Harvest Fest.

45:19.475 --> 45:20.372
Hello?

45:58.410 --> 45:59.446
Yahhh!

46:07.799 --> 46:09.836
Hey. What can I get you?

46:09.939 --> 46:11.838
- Just a dab.
- One of these?

46:11.941 --> 46:13.805
Yes, please. Thank you.

46:13.909 --> 46:15.565
- God bless.
- Bye.

46:15.669 --> 46:17.464
Come on, Grace. Yo!

46:17.567 --> 46:19.569
You don't need that shit.

46:19.673 --> 46:22.262
It's only weed. It's natural.

46:22.365 --> 46:25.437
How about instead of playing
grope-the-dope,

46:25.541 --> 46:27.612
we head over to the game booth?

46:27.715 --> 46:29.648
I'll win you a teddy bear.

46:29.752 --> 46:31.650
I'm a dead shot, you know.

46:31.754 --> 46:33.376
Chk-chk...

46:33.480 --> 46:35.585
boom!

46:35.689 --> 46:37.691
You always have been, Rel.

46:37.795 --> 46:39.072
So, give me a shot.

46:39.175 --> 46:41.281
We can leave this place
in the rearview.

46:42.661 --> 46:44.215
Like, shazam!

46:45.526 --> 46:46.907
Gone.

46:49.151 --> 46:51.947
You're a sweet guy, Rel.

46:53.845 --> 46:55.467
And a good person.

46:56.675 --> 46:58.229
Really good.

47:00.645 --> 47:02.509
Someday, you're gonna make
someone better than me

47:02.612 --> 47:03.993
so happy.

47:07.721 --> 47:11.587
♪ Then you say, "Go slow"

47:11.690 --> 47:14.521
♪ I fall behind

47:14.624 --> 47:15.729
Grace!

47:15.833 --> 47:18.145
Come to me!

47:18.249 --> 47:23.357
♪ If you're lost, you can look,
and you will find me ♪

47:23.461 --> 47:25.912
♪ Time after time

47:26.015 --> 47:30.813
♪ If you fall, I will catch you,
I'll be waiting ♪

47:30.917 --> 47:34.886
♪ Time after time

47:34.990 --> 47:37.613
I came to suck your blood!

47:37.716 --> 47:39.684
Ew, yuck. Stop.

47:39.787 --> 47:42.411
- You ready to get scared?
- Yes. Here.

47:42.514 --> 47:45.103
But you have to give me
a full two-minute lead.

47:45.207 --> 47:48.210
Okay? Because I am
getting to that bell

47:48.313 --> 47:51.730
and I'm ringing it
with everything I've got, okay?

47:51.834 --> 47:53.905
- Two minutes. Got it.
- Two minutes.

47:54.009 --> 47:56.770
Then I'm gonna find
my hot-ass devil girl.

47:56.874 --> 47:57.909
Mm.

47:58.013 --> 47:59.393
Good luck with that.

48:04.019 --> 48:08.057
You wanna join,
freaky Batman with no wings?

48:09.093 --> 48:12.165
Maybe I'll, uh, let you watch.

48:13.131 --> 48:18.067
Ha, ha, ha. No. No.
It's the Revenger!

48:18.171 --> 48:20.863
Batman doesn't have wings!

48:20.967 --> 48:23.831
You jarhead bro motherfuckers.

48:52.032 --> 48:53.171
Rel's still not picking up.

48:53.275 --> 48:54.932
We have to find him.

48:56.416 --> 48:57.865
There she is.

48:58.556 --> 49:00.282
All your friends are
getting juiced in there.

49:00.385 --> 49:02.422
I got some of my own
special sauce if you want.

49:02.525 --> 49:03.595
Hey.

49:04.907 --> 49:05.908
Hello.

49:06.012 --> 49:07.875
What are you supposed to be?

49:07.979 --> 49:08.946
A dyke?

49:11.396 --> 49:12.501
Holy shit.

49:12.604 --> 49:13.881
I learned that from you.

49:13.985 --> 49:15.676
Hey, you bitches!

49:15.780 --> 49:17.471
I wasn't gonna hurt nobody.

49:22.062 --> 49:23.408
Yeah?

49:25.272 --> 49:28.620
What about that boy
you killed with your drugs?

49:28.724 --> 49:30.346
You hurt him?

49:30.968 --> 49:32.693
I don't know what
you're talking about.

49:42.255 --> 49:44.222
This isn't over!

49:44.326 --> 49:48.226
♪ Hey, little girl

49:48.330 --> 49:51.954
♪ I long for the taste
of your lips ♪

49:52.058 --> 49:53.887
♪ Hey, little girl

49:53.991 --> 49:55.061
Yahhh!

49:56.614 --> 49:59.030
♪ I long for the crack
of your whip ♪

49:59.134 --> 50:02.240
Grace, babe, where are you?

50:02.344 --> 50:04.898
Oh, my...!

50:05.002 --> 50:07.763
Yo, if one more thing
jumps out at me...

50:07.866 --> 50:10.214
You think it's illegal to beat
the fuck out of a zombie?

50:10.317 --> 50:12.216
Don't worry, bro.
I got your back.

50:12.319 --> 50:13.320
Yahhh!

50:15.081 --> 50:16.703
Okay. Fuck this.

50:16.806 --> 50:18.187
All right, Grace!

50:18.291 --> 50:20.051
Grace, babe, where are you?

50:20.155 --> 50:21.742
Your two minutes is up!

50:39.036 --> 50:41.107
Ooooh!

50:43.523 --> 50:44.834
Gracey!

50:58.400 --> 51:00.540
Gracey...

51:10.239 --> 51:12.103
Rel, where are the others?

51:12.207 --> 51:13.691
Rel, where's Grace?

51:13.794 --> 51:15.382
Rel?

51:15.486 --> 51:17.729
I don't know.
The maze, I guess?

51:17.833 --> 51:19.076
We have to go find them.

51:19.179 --> 51:21.388
Rel, come on,
we gotta talk to them.

51:26.359 --> 51:28.844
Hey! Hey, hey! I-I hit it!

51:28.947 --> 51:30.190
I...

51:30.294 --> 51:32.192
Guys, wait! Wait up!

51:35.954 --> 51:37.818
It's for Grace.

51:37.922 --> 51:39.337
Come on.

51:41.028 --> 51:43.307
So, uh,
what's this all about?

51:46.827 --> 51:48.174
Gracey...

51:48.277 --> 51:50.866
Please pick up.
Please pick up, please pick up.

51:50.969 --> 51:52.212
Gracey...

51:56.043 --> 51:57.148
Oh!

51:59.806 --> 52:01.497
Hey, come on,
you gotta give me a clue.

52:01.601 --> 52:03.189
Dean, no, no, listen.
Listen, I'm...

52:03.292 --> 52:04.949
I'm near the center,
and this-- I don't know,

52:05.052 --> 52:07.572
this fucking crazy old woman
is trying to follow me.

52:07.676 --> 52:11.058
Babe, calm down.
It's a haunted maze.

52:11.162 --> 52:12.750
They're supposed to follow you.

52:14.545 --> 52:17.030
Dean, please.
You need to come and find me.

52:17.134 --> 52:20.896
She-- She keeps saying my name,
but I have no idea who she is.

52:20.999 --> 52:22.656
Please hurry. Please hurry.

52:22.760 --> 52:24.279
I'm lost.

52:33.805 --> 52:35.876
Gracey...

52:50.512 --> 52:52.755
Back off, you crazy old bitch!

53:02.109 --> 53:03.352
Babe?

53:03.456 --> 53:04.767
Babe, what's going on?

53:23.269 --> 53:24.511
Babe...

53:46.982 --> 53:48.397
Grace? Grace?

53:48.501 --> 53:50.813
Hey, Tan, let's go. Come on.

53:50.917 --> 53:52.125
Gracey...

53:57.061 --> 53:58.304
Help!

53:58.407 --> 53:59.719
Dean! Please!

53:59.822 --> 54:01.065
Grace, where are you?

54:01.168 --> 54:02.791
Let me know where you are.

54:02.894 --> 54:03.792
Bro, what's the rush?

54:03.895 --> 54:05.034
Grace?

54:05.138 --> 54:06.312
Somebody help me!

54:06.415 --> 54:08.969
Dean! Please!

54:09.073 --> 54:10.281
Grace!

54:10.385 --> 54:12.283
Help! Dean!

54:45.937 --> 54:47.594
Gracey!

54:51.426 --> 54:53.048
Snarls ]

54:56.396 --> 54:58.087
Help! Help!

54:58.191 --> 55:00.366
Help! Help!

55:10.203 --> 55:12.481
Help!

55:13.344 --> 55:14.725
Grace!

55:16.727 --> 55:18.315
Grace!

55:35.332 --> 55:38.404
Dean! I'm in the spiral!
I'm here!

56:22.275 --> 56:23.587
Grace! Grace!

56:46.575 --> 56:48.266
That wasn't Grace.

56:48.991 --> 56:51.511
I don't know who that was
dressed like that,

56:51.615 --> 56:52.547
but that wasn't her.

56:52.650 --> 56:54.272
It washer.

56:54.376 --> 56:56.274
She was supposed to die
of old age.

56:56.378 --> 56:58.622
What do you mean "supposed"?
She's 18!

56:58.725 --> 56:59.933
Listen!

57:01.348 --> 57:03.316
Grace is the one
who blew the whistle.

57:03.420 --> 57:05.836
But we were all with her
at the pool.

57:05.939 --> 57:08.563
Ellie's right.
We were all there.

57:10.288 --> 57:13.084
We all heard that... sound.

57:14.465 --> 57:17.157
It summoned all of our deaths.

57:17.261 --> 57:18.469
And I...

57:18.573 --> 57:20.126
I feel it watching.

57:26.028 --> 57:27.513
I've seen it, too.

57:27.616 --> 57:29.446
This morning in assembly.

57:29.549 --> 57:32.310
It was some kind of seizure.

57:32.414 --> 57:34.727
Nah, nah.
I'm-- I'm out.

57:34.830 --> 57:36.487
Hey, none of us should be alone
right now, Dean!

57:36.591 --> 57:40.249
Look, I don't know
what's going on

57:40.353 --> 57:42.113
or where Grace is,

57:42.217 --> 57:44.184
but all this spooky shit

57:44.288 --> 57:45.945
started when she came to town.

57:46.048 --> 57:47.671
Are you kidding me?

57:49.155 --> 57:52.020
You dared her
to blow that fucking whistle.

57:52.123 --> 57:54.471
You pushed her to do it.

57:54.574 --> 57:57.094
It's your fault she's dead!

57:58.302 --> 58:00.269
Hey! Dean, Dean!

58:00.373 --> 58:01.892
Stop!

58:05.205 --> 58:07.311
We get it.

58:07.414 --> 58:09.555
You had a little crush.

58:10.487 --> 58:12.489
But people like you...

58:13.317 --> 58:15.457
...don't ever stand a chance.

58:28.056 --> 58:28.953
Rel.

58:29.057 --> 58:30.161
Rel!

58:33.337 --> 58:35.235
Keep playing "Scooby Doo."

58:35.926 --> 58:39.274
I'm gonna go get smashed
and wait till Grace gets home.

59:12.445 --> 59:13.619
Dean...

59:33.328 --> 59:35.572
Dean? Is that you?

59:35.675 --> 59:37.815
It's okay. I just...
I just had a nightmare.

59:37.919 --> 59:39.645
You woke your mother up.
She's gotta be at the store...

59:39.748 --> 59:41.474
Yeah, just go back to bed.

59:42.130 --> 59:45.133
You better not be drinking
and driving again, son.

59:46.548 --> 59:48.067
It'll be the death of you.

01:00:03.772 --> 01:00:06.188
- How's he doing?
- He's heartbroken.

01:00:06.292 --> 01:00:09.088
Been in love with Grace
since they were kids, so...

01:00:12.919 --> 01:00:14.956
Um, find anything on In Choka?

01:00:15.059 --> 01:00:15.784
Not really.

01:00:15.888 --> 01:00:17.475
Just some New age cults

01:00:17.579 --> 01:00:18.960
and some scams.

01:00:23.620 --> 01:00:25.932
But we need to find a way
to stop it.

01:00:26.036 --> 01:00:29.108
Yeah. We should go back
to Ms. Raymore tomorrow.

01:00:32.421 --> 01:00:34.769
Have you ever seen anyone die?

01:00:37.668 --> 01:00:40.567
A few. In the hospital.

01:00:45.676 --> 01:00:48.161
I OD'd about a year ago.

01:00:50.888 --> 01:00:53.580
My dad found me
and he drove me to the hospital,

01:00:53.684 --> 01:00:55.099
and we were...

01:00:56.411 --> 01:00:58.171
We were half a mile away, and...

01:00:58.965 --> 01:01:00.691
...a truck hit us.

01:01:01.899 --> 01:01:03.452
I'm so sorry.

01:01:09.010 --> 01:01:10.908
Now I've got his...

01:01:11.012 --> 01:01:13.117
his music, you know, I...

01:01:14.394 --> 01:01:16.017
I listen to it.

01:01:17.570 --> 01:01:19.917
Makes me feel connected, like...

01:01:20.021 --> 01:01:21.712
Like a bridge, I guess.

01:01:21.816 --> 01:01:23.783
He had good taste.

01:01:23.887 --> 01:01:27.511
♪ But we got lucky
once before ♪

01:01:27.614 --> 01:01:31.584
♪ And I don't wanna
close the door ♪

01:01:31.688 --> 01:01:35.243
My actions killed my dad,
and there's...

01:01:36.727 --> 01:01:39.005
There's nothing
I can do about it.

01:01:41.214 --> 01:01:43.838
Sometimes I wish it had been me.

01:01:46.357 --> 01:01:47.600
But it wasn't.

01:01:47.704 --> 01:01:49.119
And you're here.

01:02:00.302 --> 01:02:03.512
I just finished telling you
how fucked up I am.

01:02:05.860 --> 01:02:07.758
Everyone's fucked up.

01:02:07.862 --> 01:02:10.209
You just happen to know it.

01:02:11.935 --> 01:02:14.800
And that shit you pulled
with Noah...

01:02:16.318 --> 01:02:17.975
That was really cool.

01:02:19.425 --> 01:02:21.116
Yeah, but you've got
your shit together.

01:02:21.220 --> 01:02:24.188
You know, you're-- you're smart
and you're funny, and...

01:02:25.293 --> 01:02:26.777
And I'm just...

01:02:30.539 --> 01:02:32.162
You're Chrysanthemum.

01:02:32.265 --> 01:02:36.062
♪ But if it's love
you're looking for ♪

01:02:36.166 --> 01:02:40.204
♪ Then I can give
a little more ♪

01:02:40.308 --> 01:02:46.866
♪ And if you're somewhere drunk
and passed out on the floor ♪

01:02:46.970 --> 01:02:57.049
♪ Oh, Joey,
I'm not angry anymore ♪

01:03:05.989 --> 01:03:09.233
You're insane.
That was not her.

01:03:09.889 --> 01:03:12.374
Our future death
is hunting us.

01:03:12.478 --> 01:03:17.690
We were all there.
We all heard that... sound.

01:03:22.591 --> 01:03:25.663
I started working weekends
at the steel mill.

01:03:26.803 --> 01:03:28.011
...the steel mill...

01:03:28.114 --> 01:03:30.565
We all heard that... sound.

01:03:33.292 --> 01:03:35.881
It summoned all of our deaths.

01:03:56.211 --> 01:03:59.180
Please don't be too long.
She's taken a bit of a turn.

01:04:07.429 --> 01:04:08.914
It took our friend.

01:04:09.017 --> 01:04:10.777
What does it want?

01:04:10.881 --> 01:04:12.814
The Olmec offered souls

01:04:12.918 --> 01:04:16.059
to Satiate their gods of death.

01:04:16.749 --> 01:04:21.133
In Choka has been collecting
them for thousands of years.

01:04:21.236 --> 01:04:24.653
But it's not our time,
and we need to stop it.

01:04:24.757 --> 01:04:27.070
Death is unstoppable.

01:04:28.347 --> 01:04:32.489
Once called, it will not relent.

01:04:34.871 --> 01:04:38.219
But there is a way
to change its course.

01:04:38.322 --> 01:04:39.841
But how?

01:04:39.945 --> 01:04:42.016
How-- How do we change
its course?

01:04:43.017 --> 01:04:45.433
Give your death...

01:04:45.536 --> 01:04:47.573
someone else's life.

01:04:49.471 --> 01:04:51.025
What do you mean?

01:04:51.128 --> 01:04:53.130
Offer In Choka...

01:04:54.200 --> 01:04:56.202
...a new sacrifice.

01:04:58.515 --> 01:05:00.551
When your death is near,

01:05:00.655 --> 01:05:03.589
mark another with your blood,

01:05:03.692 --> 01:05:05.556
and you will be spared.

01:05:06.764 --> 01:05:08.732
Mark them with our blood?

01:05:08.835 --> 01:05:11.010
No. No, we can't do that.

01:05:13.702 --> 01:05:17.810
Dying is not a choice.

01:05:19.329 --> 01:05:22.746
Chrysanthemum...

01:05:29.201 --> 01:05:31.306
It is inevitable.

01:05:38.555 --> 01:05:40.177
But living...

01:05:44.112 --> 01:05:45.907
...that's up to you.

01:05:56.193 --> 01:05:58.644
- I think she was ready.
- Well, I'm not ready.

01:05:58.747 --> 01:06:00.542
And she just told us
exactly what we need to know.

01:06:00.646 --> 01:06:04.270
No. I veto any solution
that requires murder.

01:06:04.374 --> 01:06:07.411
So what, that's it?
We just wait to die?

01:06:11.450 --> 01:06:13.486
I saw her.

01:06:13.590 --> 01:06:15.074
My death.

01:06:17.904 --> 01:06:19.596
I O.D.

01:06:21.011 --> 01:06:22.461
With a needle in my arm.

01:06:22.564 --> 01:06:24.014
Chrys...

01:06:24.808 --> 01:06:26.085
I don't want to use again.

01:06:26.189 --> 01:06:27.155
I don't want to hurt
people again.

01:06:27.259 --> 01:06:29.088
I don't want to hurt myself.

01:06:30.227 --> 01:06:31.988
I'd rather die.

01:06:32.609 --> 01:06:34.921
Look, I-I'm sorry,
but we are running out of time.

01:06:35.025 --> 01:06:37.786
We've all seen our deaths,
and they're coming for us next,

01:06:37.890 --> 01:06:39.340
so we don't have a choice now.

01:06:39.443 --> 01:06:42.274
No, Rel, we'll be okay
if we stick together.

01:06:42.377 --> 01:06:44.172
Do you really believe that?

01:06:47.313 --> 01:06:49.453
- Rel...
- I just need to think!

01:06:49.557 --> 01:06:50.592
Okay?

01:06:58.014 --> 01:06:59.636
Rel! Stop!

01:07:02.915 --> 01:07:03.985
I'll call Dean.

01:07:20.864 --> 01:07:23.901
And we return now to
a local report in Pellington,

01:07:24.005 --> 01:07:27.560
to the tragic events of
last night's Harvest Festival.

01:07:28.492 --> 01:07:32.289
Just moments ago, paramedics
removed a body from the scene.

01:07:32.393 --> 01:07:34.360
At this time, we don't have
a lot of information,

01:07:34.464 --> 01:07:37.950
but what we do know is that the
woman has yet to be identified.

01:07:38.054 --> 01:07:41.471
Police are asking anyone who
may know her to come forward.

01:07:41.574 --> 01:07:44.646
In the meantime,
it is a very hectic situation

01:07:44.750 --> 01:07:46.200
right here on the ground.

01:07:46.303 --> 01:07:48.443
Police have completely
taped off the area

01:07:48.547 --> 01:07:50.342
as they continue
their investigation.

01:07:50.445 --> 01:07:52.240
We are standing by,
and as soon as we...

01:08:03.803 --> 01:08:04.908
Mom?

01:08:06.806 --> 01:08:08.153
Dad?

01:08:15.263 --> 01:08:16.747
Mom, is that you?

01:08:19.923 --> 01:08:21.200
Mom.

01:08:28.380 --> 01:08:29.450
Dad?

01:08:40.288 --> 01:08:41.876
Dean...

01:08:44.016 --> 01:08:46.225
Leave me alone!

01:08:46.329 --> 01:08:48.607
Dean? What the hell
is going on in there?

01:08:48.710 --> 01:08:50.126
Dad? No, no! No! Dad!

01:08:52.404 --> 01:08:53.784
Dad, do you see it?

01:08:53.888 --> 01:08:54.923
Is he all right?

01:08:55.027 --> 01:08:56.373
Dean, open the door.

01:08:56.477 --> 01:08:58.272
You're scaring your mother.
- I...I can't!

01:08:58.375 --> 01:09:00.722
What's going on?

01:09:00.826 --> 01:09:02.448
Baby, just open the door.

01:09:02.552 --> 01:09:04.347
- I-I can't.
- Dean, open the door.

01:09:04.450 --> 01:09:05.934
- It'll get in.
- What are you talking about?

01:09:06.038 --> 01:09:07.281
Dean! Come on, honey.

01:09:07.384 --> 01:09:09.214
Look, I need you
to listen to me, please!

01:09:09.317 --> 01:09:10.525
Let us in!

01:09:10.629 --> 01:09:11.630
Please.

01:09:21.605 --> 01:09:23.020
Dean!

01:09:23.124 --> 01:09:24.539
What's going on in there, Dean?

01:09:24.643 --> 01:09:25.816
Come on, honey!

01:09:50.634 --> 01:09:51.670
Dean!

01:10:15.314 --> 01:10:16.522
Rel?

01:10:21.803 --> 01:10:22.735
Rel?

01:10:29.846 --> 01:10:31.227
Revenger.

01:10:34.091 --> 01:10:36.093
Ellie. Where is this?

01:10:36.922 --> 01:10:39.649
It's the steel mill
on the other side of town.

01:10:45.171 --> 01:10:46.621
Shit!

01:10:46.725 --> 01:10:47.829
What is it?

01:10:57.183 --> 01:10:59.013
Be safe, everyone.

01:11:01.395 --> 01:11:03.362
Same time next week.

01:11:03.466 --> 01:11:05.847
Thank you.
Thanks for coming.

01:11:19.378 --> 01:11:22.657
♪ Are you washed in the blood
of the lamb? ♪

01:11:24.107 --> 01:11:28.767
♪ Are you fully trusting
in His grace and power? ♪

01:11:32.529 --> 01:11:34.255
Don't make this difficult.

01:11:34.359 --> 01:11:35.498
The fuck is this?

01:11:35.601 --> 01:11:37.293
Guy at the mill sold it to me.

01:11:37.396 --> 01:11:39.260
It's loaded.

01:11:39.364 --> 01:11:40.606
What are you doing, man?

01:11:40.710 --> 01:11:44.023
You have to do what I say, okay?

01:11:44.127 --> 01:11:45.853
Oh, do I?

01:11:45.956 --> 01:11:48.545
I bet you don't even know
how to use that thing.

01:11:52.860 --> 01:11:54.310
Fuck!

01:11:58.348 --> 01:11:59.729
Now...

01:12:04.768 --> 01:12:05.873
Motherfucker!

01:12:18.644 --> 01:12:20.646
You're done now, my friend.

01:12:21.992 --> 01:12:23.787
You are so fucking done.

01:12:32.106 --> 01:12:34.073
What's so funny?

01:12:34.177 --> 01:12:36.317
You don't get it.

01:12:36.421 --> 01:12:38.699
I don't die this way.

01:12:40.701 --> 01:12:42.875
You fucking freak.

01:12:42.979 --> 01:12:45.706
Hey! I warned you!

01:12:48.087 --> 01:12:49.123
Shit!

01:12:49.226 --> 01:12:51.505
Fuck! Fuck!

01:13:08.073 --> 01:13:11.179
What's the point of dragging me
all the way out here?

01:13:11.283 --> 01:13:13.527
This is where I'll die.

01:13:13.630 --> 01:13:15.356
So this is where
you're gonna die.

01:13:15.460 --> 01:13:16.702
What?

01:13:17.600 --> 01:13:19.636
What, are you insane?
Huh?

01:13:29.128 --> 01:13:30.406
This what you give them?

01:13:30.509 --> 01:13:31.752
Your, uh...

01:13:33.029 --> 01:13:34.306
...young believers?

01:13:34.410 --> 01:13:37.136
You want some?
They're all yours.

01:13:38.344 --> 01:13:40.036
Go ahead and take 'em.

01:13:40.139 --> 01:13:41.486
How many does it take?

01:13:41.589 --> 01:13:42.659
One will make you happy,

01:13:42.763 --> 01:13:44.592
two will make you fly.

01:13:44.696 --> 01:13:46.007
I'll go for three.

01:13:47.423 --> 01:13:49.355
Swallow. Swallow!

01:13:54.291 --> 01:13:55.603
Swallow.

01:14:02.196 --> 01:14:04.750
Hey, man, can you please
just tell me what this is about?

01:14:04.854 --> 01:14:05.924
Huh?

01:14:07.201 --> 01:14:08.996
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.

01:14:09.099 --> 01:14:10.549
Hey. Hey.

01:14:12.482 --> 01:14:13.690
Jesus Christ!

01:14:13.794 --> 01:14:16.693
Hey, let-- let's talk
about this, man.

01:14:19.593 --> 01:14:22.492
What is that thing, huh?

01:14:22.596 --> 01:14:24.701
Is that witchcraft, man?

01:14:24.805 --> 01:14:28.084
Is that what you're into?
You're a Satanist?

01:14:30.051 --> 01:14:31.639
Hey, look...

01:14:34.159 --> 01:14:36.057
Death is close.

01:14:44.238 --> 01:14:45.377
I gotta mark you now.

01:14:45.481 --> 01:14:46.999
What?

01:14:47.552 --> 01:14:49.346
No, you don't have to mark me,
man!

01:14:49.450 --> 01:14:51.176
Get that shit away from me!

01:14:51.279 --> 01:14:52.591
Rel!

01:14:52.695 --> 01:14:54.420
Rel, you don't have to do this!

01:14:54.524 --> 01:14:55.456
Ellie!

01:14:55.560 --> 01:14:57.803
Rel. Put the gun down.

01:14:57.907 --> 01:15:00.081
- It's not fair.
- Rel, put the gun down.

01:15:00.185 --> 01:15:03.360
A murdering scumbag like him
gets to live,

01:15:03.464 --> 01:15:07.744
while you or me or Grace dies?

01:15:07.848 --> 01:15:10.022
You think that makes
any sense at all?

01:15:12.197 --> 01:15:14.440
- It doesn't make any sense.
- Rel...

01:15:14.544 --> 01:15:15.441
Stop.

01:15:15.545 --> 01:15:18.030
Stay back.

01:15:20.654 --> 01:15:22.103
Please, Jesus. Please, God.

01:15:22.207 --> 01:15:23.795
I will be your instrument.
I seek forgiveness.

01:15:23.898 --> 01:15:25.590
- Shut up!
- I'm sorry for what I've done.

01:15:25.693 --> 01:15:27.453
I sold him my shit.
I didn't mean for him to die.

01:15:27.557 --> 01:15:29.559
- You murdered that boy!
- It was an accident.

01:15:29.663 --> 01:15:31.630
- You killed him!
- I didn't know, all right?

01:15:31.734 --> 01:15:32.873
I didn't know he was gonna die.

01:15:32.976 --> 01:15:34.357
- Shut up!
- I'm not a bad person.

01:15:34.460 --> 01:15:35.945
I'm washed in the blood.

01:15:36.048 --> 01:15:37.671
Jesus, I will be the hammer
in your hand, Lord.

01:15:37.774 --> 01:15:39.638
So help me God,
just fucking save me now.

01:15:39.742 --> 01:15:41.295
Rel, please!

01:15:41.398 --> 01:15:43.297
Rel, stop! Don't do it!

01:15:43.400 --> 01:15:46.231
This is wrong. Stop, okay?

01:15:46.334 --> 01:15:48.302
You don't have to do this.

01:15:48.405 --> 01:15:50.442
- Please.
- We can fix it.

01:15:50.546 --> 01:15:52.755
Please, Rel. Please.

01:15:52.858 --> 01:15:53.963
Rel.

01:16:06.078 --> 01:16:07.666
Thank you, Jesus.

01:16:09.185 --> 01:16:12.809
I am marked only by God.
I am marked only by God.

01:16:12.913 --> 01:16:16.157
I am marked only by God.
And I am delivered.

01:16:22.647 --> 01:16:25.166
I guess everyone
has to die once.

01:16:28.307 --> 01:16:29.826
Say that again?

01:16:29.930 --> 01:16:32.070
I said everyone has to die.

01:16:33.312 --> 01:16:34.762
You said once.

01:16:35.763 --> 01:16:36.902
That's it.

01:16:37.006 --> 01:16:38.352
That's it.
That's how we stop this.

01:16:38.455 --> 01:16:39.767
How?

01:16:43.046 --> 01:16:45.359
Oh, shit...

01:16:48.604 --> 01:16:50.019
It's here.

01:16:51.089 --> 01:16:52.297
What's here?

01:17:09.935 --> 01:17:12.973
Rel...

01:17:13.076 --> 01:17:15.078
Rel, what's going on?
What is it?

01:17:16.528 --> 01:17:18.116
Rel...

01:17:24.709 --> 01:17:27.470
No! No!

01:17:30.680 --> 01:17:31.957
Get him back!

01:17:32.061 --> 01:17:34.753
What the fuck?!

01:17:49.250 --> 01:17:50.389
Rel!

01:17:57.086 --> 01:17:58.432
Chrys...

01:18:25.148 --> 01:18:27.461
It's not your fault.
There's nothing we can do.

01:18:27.564 --> 01:18:29.843
Chrys. Chrys, we have to go.

01:18:29.946 --> 01:18:31.845
We have to go!

01:18:31.948 --> 01:18:34.123
You said there's a way
out of this.

01:18:36.056 --> 01:18:38.058
I'm not letting it get you.

01:18:47.515 --> 01:18:48.896
So, what's the plan?

01:18:49.000 --> 01:18:51.278
We summoned death,
and we can't outrun it.

01:18:51.381 --> 01:18:53.038
Now we have to die.

01:18:54.108 --> 01:18:56.317
That doesn't mean
we have to stay dead.

01:18:57.802 --> 01:18:59.424
Is this all you've got?

01:19:02.979 --> 01:19:06.258
I carry backup insulin
for emergencies.

01:19:06.362 --> 01:19:07.570
How much do you need?

01:19:07.673 --> 01:19:09.434
Enough to stop a heart.

01:19:09.537 --> 01:19:12.713
Insulin won't be enough
to trigger a cardiac arrest.

01:19:12.817 --> 01:19:14.370
Uh...

01:19:14.473 --> 01:19:15.681
I have an idea.

01:19:24.621 --> 01:19:25.691
Bring it all!

01:20:53.607 --> 01:20:55.574
Okay, so, one more time.

01:20:55.678 --> 01:20:57.024
I inject you,

01:20:57.128 --> 01:20:59.026
make sure you have no pulse,
no heartbeat,

01:20:59.130 --> 01:21:01.339
so you're technically dead.

01:21:03.720 --> 01:21:06.309
And then the glucagon,
so we don't go hypoglycemic

01:21:06.413 --> 01:21:08.864
when the defibrillator
kick-starts the heart.

01:21:15.215 --> 01:21:17.148
Okay. Hand me one of those.

01:21:17.251 --> 01:21:19.288
I'll-- I'll do you,
and you can do me.

01:21:20.254 --> 01:21:21.842
I have to make sure you live.

01:21:37.858 --> 01:21:38.928
I'm sorry.

01:21:39.032 --> 01:21:40.205
No...

01:21:47.626 --> 01:21:49.042
Ellie!

01:21:49.905 --> 01:21:51.320
Chrys!

01:21:54.081 --> 01:21:55.634
I'm sorry!

01:22:31.877 --> 01:22:33.224
Glucagon.

01:22:44.200 --> 01:22:46.616
Thank you, Lord.

01:22:46.720 --> 01:22:48.756
Thank you for saving me.

01:22:48.860 --> 01:22:51.035
Thank you for saving me.

01:22:51.138 --> 01:22:52.622
Please work.

01:23:02.978 --> 01:23:04.565
Okay. Okay.

01:23:08.707 --> 01:23:09.881
Okay.

01:23:25.897 --> 01:23:27.347
Chrys.

01:23:27.450 --> 01:23:28.382
No.

01:23:28.486 --> 01:23:30.074
Chrys. Come on.

01:23:30.177 --> 01:23:33.215
Chrys. No!

01:23:33.318 --> 01:23:34.457
Come on.

01:23:35.769 --> 01:23:37.391
Chrys, come on. Come on.

01:24:09.354 --> 01:24:11.667
- Come on.
- I can hear you.

01:24:33.482 --> 01:24:36.795
No. Not yet.
Not yet, not yet, not yet!

01:24:37.831 --> 01:24:39.833
Come on, come on!

01:24:48.876 --> 01:24:51.672
Death is unstoppable.

01:24:51.776 --> 01:24:55.814
Once called,
it will not relent.

01:25:03.339 --> 01:25:05.445
What kind of Satan shit
is this?

01:25:08.551 --> 01:25:10.657
Aah!

01:25:29.986 --> 01:25:31.919
Chrys, come on.

01:25:32.023 --> 01:25:34.267
Come back to me.

01:25:34.370 --> 01:25:36.234
Please!

01:25:38.581 --> 01:25:41.998
Come back to me.
I need you to live!

01:25:51.767 --> 01:25:53.872
Chrysanthemum.

01:25:53.976 --> 01:25:56.496
Chrysanthemum.

01:25:56.599 --> 01:25:57.842
Chrysanthemum!

01:25:57.945 --> 01:26:03.054
Dying is not a choice.

01:26:03.158 --> 01:26:05.712
It is inevitable.

01:26:07.196 --> 01:26:08.956
But living...

01:26:13.375 --> 01:26:15.100
...that's up to you.

01:26:15.204 --> 01:26:16.412
Ellie!

01:26:16.516 --> 01:26:18.552
You're Chrysanthemum.

01:26:21.831 --> 01:26:23.178
Ellie!

01:26:28.286 --> 01:26:30.254
Ellie!

01:26:32.048 --> 01:26:33.843
Ellie!

01:27:00.939 --> 01:27:02.078
Wake up.

01:27:04.219 --> 01:27:05.772
No!

01:27:05.875 --> 01:27:07.739
You stay away from her!

01:27:11.398 --> 01:27:13.331
It's like I told you.

01:27:13.435 --> 01:27:15.713
God's got a job for everyone.

01:27:16.334 --> 01:27:19.786
I'm just trying
to help those in need.

01:27:20.787 --> 01:27:22.202
But you...

01:27:22.306 --> 01:27:25.136
you're beyond redemption.

01:27:25.240 --> 01:27:26.758
Whereas I...

01:27:26.862 --> 01:27:29.727
I am washed
in the blood of the lamb.

01:27:33.317 --> 01:27:34.904
Yeah.

01:27:49.747 --> 01:27:51.369
May the body of our Lord
Jesus Christ

01:27:51.473 --> 01:27:54.234
preserve your soul
in life everlasting.

01:27:54.338 --> 01:27:55.580
Amen.

01:28:04.762 --> 01:28:08.179
Are you fully
trusting in his grace and power?

01:28:08.283 --> 01:28:09.870
Hey...

01:28:09.974 --> 01:28:11.527
The fuck?

01:28:13.564 --> 01:28:15.462
Noah...

01:28:15.566 --> 01:28:18.465
What? Do you hear me?
No. Stay back!

01:29:01.646 --> 01:29:03.061
Hey. Hey.

01:29:08.101 --> 01:29:10.034
Stay, stay, stay.

01:29:12.761 --> 01:29:14.349
I'm sorry.

01:29:17.213 --> 01:29:19.008
Hell of a first date, huh?

01:29:23.668 --> 01:29:24.842
Chrys...

01:30:37.535 --> 01:30:40.952
It's been three months,
two weeks, and four days.

01:30:43.438 --> 01:30:45.232
I count each and every
one of them now.

01:30:45.336 --> 01:30:51.929
♪ Keeping secrets
until everything became
a bit too loud ♪

01:30:53.378 --> 01:30:56.243
I always thought
death was the enemy.

01:30:56.347 --> 01:30:58.245
But now I'm not so sure.

01:30:58.349 --> 01:31:00.351
♪ I could drown it out

01:31:00.455 --> 01:31:02.215
No one has forever.

01:31:04.113 --> 01:31:05.943
But we do have right now.

01:31:06.046 --> 01:31:09.809
♪ By writing sentences I used
to think were quite profound ♪

01:31:09.912 --> 01:31:12.087
I think I can live with that.

01:31:15.435 --> 01:31:21.510
♪ And it feels like the weight
is too much to carry ♪

01:31:21.614 --> 01:31:27.171
♪ I should quit,
maybe go get married ♪

01:31:27.274 --> 01:31:33.004
♪ Only time will tell

01:31:37.112 --> 01:31:39.528
♪ In the final cut

01:31:39.632 --> 01:31:42.013
♪ In the final scene

01:31:42.117 --> 01:31:44.533
♪ There's a final girl

01:31:44.637 --> 01:31:47.294
♪ Does she look like me?

01:31:47.398 --> 01:31:49.711
♪ In the final cut

01:31:49.814 --> 01:31:52.334
♪ In the final scene

01:31:52.437 --> 01:31:54.854
♪ There's a final girl

01:31:54.957 --> 01:31:59.134
♪ And you know that she
should be screaming now ♪

01:32:13.286 --> 01:32:16.082
Asha...

01:32:19.464 --> 01:32:21.570
Asha...

01:32:39.277 --> 01:32:42.108
♪ Oh, yeah

01:32:42.211 --> 01:32:43.281
♪ Yeah

01:32:47.044 --> 01:32:50.081
♪ Oh, yeah

01:33:04.026 --> 01:33:07.858
♪ Oh, yeah

01:33:11.586 --> 01:33:15.106
♪ Oh, yeah

01:33:28.672 --> 01:33:31.364
♪ Ooh, yeah

01:33:41.098 --> 01:33:42.720
♪ You walk through the subway

01:33:42.824 --> 01:33:45.654
♪ His eyes burn a hole
in your back ♪

01:33:46.793 --> 01:33:48.139
♪ A footstep behind you

01:33:48.243 --> 01:33:51.142
♪ He lunges,
prepared for attack ♪

01:33:52.627 --> 01:33:55.181
♪ Scream for mercy

01:33:55.284 --> 01:33:58.184
♪ He laughs
as he's watching you bleed ♪

01:33:58.287 --> 01:34:00.669
♪ Killer behind you

01:34:00.773 --> 01:34:04.293
♪ His bloodlust defies
all his needs ♪

01:34:05.536 --> 01:34:06.882
Good morning, everyone.

01:34:06.986 --> 01:34:08.884
As is customary here
at Pellington High,

01:34:08.988 --> 01:34:10.506
to begin the new semester,

01:34:10.610 --> 01:34:13.095
we welcome freshman student
Asha Nelson,

01:34:13.199 --> 01:34:16.443
who will be playing
our school anthem on her violin.

01:34:43.712 --> 01:34:45.162
- Wait! Stop!
- Stop!

01:34:45.265 --> 01:34:47.440
- Stop!
- Stop! Stop!

01:34:47.543 --> 01:34:49.545
Stop!
